Create function to get target frequency by categorical column level.¶

In [8]:
def target_count(df,target):
    for col in tqdm_notebook(train.columns[3:60]):
        temp=pd.DataFrame()
        df1=pd.crosstab(df[col],df[target],normalize='columns').reset_index()
        temp[f"{col}"]=df1[f"{col}"]
        temp[f"{col}_{target}_n"]=df1.iloc[:,0]
        temp[f"{col}_{target}_y"]=df1.iloc[:,1]
        df=pd.merge(df,temp, on=col,how='left')
    return df

In [16]:
def feature_imp_plot(df,feat_imp_score,title="" ):
    _=plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
    feat_importance=pd.DataFrame({'columns':df.columns,'score':feat_imp_score})
    feat_importance=feat_importance.sort_values('score',ascending=False)
    _=sns.barplot(data=feat_importance.nlargest(10,'score'),x='score',y='columns')
    plt.title(f"{title}",fontsize=16);
